Responses.NAM1 - Response Text: Do you want the blessings of the Tribunal?
Imperial cult members, or reverent, respectful guests, may make offerings at shrines and receive in return a blessing.
Common blessings are healing, cure common or blight disease, resistance to common or blight disease, cure poison, and other health benefits.
More extraordinary blessings are reserved for the advanced ranks of the faithful. No offering need be made by these pious souls;
benefits may include long-term fortification of attributes and abilities.
